22/11/2002
TIRANA, Albania -- Local authorities and international organisations working with the Stability Pact for Southeast Europe met in Tirana on Thursday (21 November) for a conference on the environment. 
The Albanian Ministry of Environment and Regional Environment Centre for Central and Eastern Europe were the major sponsors of the event. 
Environment Minister Lufter Xhuveli said the problems of environmental protection in the Balkans depend on adoption of adequate laws and implementation in countries across the region. 
He proposed a list of measures to support and assist implementation of international conventions and agreements. 
(ATA - 21/11/02)
